                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d83">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-09-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 23, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Adee states that the date for signing completed treaty, October 8, is
                    absolute and not contingent on action of Russia. This date has been formally
                    accepted by the Chinese Government and this Government notified. By the
                    Department’s telegraphic instruction of August 15 Mr. Conger was told to make
                    this clear to Prince Ch’ing, and Mr. Conger is directed to so inform the Prince
                    again. * * *</p>
            </div>
